The paper deals with visual recognition problems, specifically group activity recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a method that integrates graphical models and deep neural networks, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of gates on edges between nodes, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) analysis.
